40static const uint8_t PAD = 129;
41static const uint8_t UPPER_SHIFT = 235;
42static const uint8_t MACRO_05 = 236;
43static const uint8_t MACRO_06 = 237;
44static const uint8_t C40_UNLATCH = 254;
45static const uint8_t X12_UNLATCH = 254;
46
47static const std::wstring MACRO_05_HEADER = L"[)>\x1E""05\x1D";
48static const std::wstring MACRO_06_HEADER = L"[)>\x1E""06\x1D";
49static const std::wstring MACRO_TRAILER = L"\x1E\x04";
50
51enum
52{
53 ASCII_ENCODATION,
54 C40_ENCODATION,
55 TEXT_ENCODATION,
56 X12_ENCODATION,
57 EDIFACT_ENCODATION,
58 BASE256_ENCODATION,
59};
60
61static const uint8_t LATCHES[] = {
62 0, // ASCII mode, no latch needed
63 230, // LATCH_TO_C40
64 239, // LATCH_TO_TEXT
65 238, // LATCH_TO_ANSIX12
66 240, // LATCH_TO_EDIFACT
67 231, // LATCH_TO_BASE256,
68};

70static inline bool IsDigit(int ch)
71{
72 return ch >= '0' && ch <= '9';
73}
74
75static inline bool IsExtendedASCII(int ch)
76{
77 return ch >= 128 && ch <= 255;
78}
79
80static inline bool IsNativeC40(int ch)
81{
82 return (ch == ' ') || (ch >= '0' && ch <= '9') || (ch >= 'A' && ch <= 'Z');
83}
84
85static inline bool IsNativeText(int ch)
86{
87 return (ch == ' ') || (ch >= '0' && ch <= '9') || (ch >= 'a' && ch <= 'z');
88}
89
90static inline bool IsX12TermSep(int ch)
91{
92 return (ch == '\r') //CR
93 || (ch == '*')
94 || (ch == '>');
95}
96
97static inline bool IsNativeX12(int ch)
98{
99 return IsX12TermSep(ch) || (ch == ' ') || (ch >= '0' && ch <= '9') || (ch >= 'A' && ch <= 'Z');
100}
101
102static inline bool IsNativeEDIFACT(int ch)
103{
104 return ch >= ' ' && ch <= '^';
105}
106
107static inline bool IsSpecialB256(int /*ch*/)
108{
109 return false; //TODO NOT IMPLEMENTED YET!!!
110}

127static uint8_t Randomize253State(uint8_t ch, int codewordPosition)
128{
129 int pseudoRandom = ((149 * codewordPosition) % 253) + 1;
130 int tempVariable = ch + pseudoRandom;
131 return static_cast<uint8_t>(tempVariable <= 254 ? tempVariable : (tempVariable - 254));
132}
133
134static int FindMinimums(const std::array<int, 6>& intCharCounts, int min, std::array<int, 6>& mins)
135{
136 mins.fill(0);
137 for (int i = 0; i < 6; i++) {
138 int current = intCharCounts[i];
139 if (min > current) {
140 min = current;
141 mins.fill(0);
142 }
143 if (min == current) {
144 mins[i]++;
145 }
146 }
147 return min;
148}
149
150static int LookAheadTest(const std::string& msg, size_t startpos, int currentMode)
151{
152 if (startpos >= msg.length()) {
153 return currentMode;
154 }
155 std::array<float, 6> charCounts;
156 //step J
157 if (currentMode == ASCII_ENCODATION) {
158 charCounts = { 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1.25f };
159 }
160 else {
161 charCounts = { 1, 2, 2, 2, 2, 2.25f };
162 charCounts[currentMode] = 0;
163 }
164
165 std::array<int, 6> mins;
166 std::array<int, 6> intCharCounts;
167 int charsProcessed = 0;
168 while (true) {
169 //step K
170 if ((startpos + charsProcessed) == msg.length()) {
171 int min = std::numeric_limits<int>::max();
172 std::transform(charCounts.begin(), charCounts.end(), intCharCounts.begin(), [](float x) { return static_cast<int>(std::ceil(x)); });
173 min = FindMinimums(intCharCounts, min, mins);
174 int minCount = std::accumulate(mins.begin(), mins.end(), 0);
175
176 if (intCharCounts[ASCII_ENCODATION] == min) {
177 return ASCII_ENCODATION;
178 }
179 if (minCount == 1 && mins[BASE256_ENCODATION] > 0) {
180 return BASE256_ENCODATION;
181 }
182 if (minCount == 1 && mins[EDIFACT_ENCODATION] > 0) {
183 return EDIFACT_ENCODATION;
184 }
185 if (minCount == 1 && mins[TEXT_ENCODATION] > 0) {
186 return TEXT_ENCODATION;
187 }
188 if (minCount == 1 && mins[X12_ENCODATION] > 0) {
189 return X12_ENCODATION;
190 }
191 return C40_ENCODATION;
192 }
193
194 int c = (uint8_t)msg.at(startpos + charsProcessed);
195 charsProcessed++;
196
197 //step L
198 if (IsDigit(c)) {
199 charCounts[ASCII_ENCODATION] += 0.5f;
200 }
201 else if (IsExtendedASCII(c)) {
202 charCounts[ASCII_ENCODATION] = std::ceil(charCounts[ASCII_ENCODATION]);
203 charCounts[ASCII_ENCODATION] += 2.0f;
204 }
205 else {
206 charCounts[ASCII_ENCODATION] = std::ceil(charCounts[ASCII_ENCODATION]);
207 charCounts[ASCII_ENCODATION] += 1.0f;
208 }
209
210 //step M
211 if (IsNativeC40(c)) {
212 charCounts[C40_ENCODATION] += 2.0f / 3.0f;
213 }
214 else if (IsExtendedASCII(c)) {
215 charCounts[C40_ENCODATION] += 8.0f / 3.0f;
216 }
217 else {
218 charCounts[C40_ENCODATION] += 4.0f / 3.0f;
219 }
220
221 //step N
222 if (IsNativeText(c)) {
223 charCounts[TEXT_ENCODATION] += 2.0f / 3.0f;
224 }
225 else if (IsExtendedASCII(c)) {
226 charCounts[TEXT_ENCODATION] += 8.0f / 3.0f;
227 }
228 else {
229 charCounts[TEXT_ENCODATION] += 4.0f / 3.0f;
230 }
231
232 //step O
233 if (IsNativeX12(c)) {
234 charCounts[X12_ENCODATION] += 2.0f / 3.0f;
235 }
236 else if (IsExtendedASCII(c)) {
237 charCounts[X12_ENCODATION] += 13.0f / 3.0f;
238 }
239 else {
240 charCounts[X12_ENCODATION] += 10.0f / 3.0f;
241 }
242
243 //step P
244 if (IsNativeEDIFACT(c)) {
245 charCounts[EDIFACT_ENCODATION] += 3.0f / 4.0f;
246 }
247 else if (IsExtendedASCII(c)) {
248 charCounts[EDIFACT_ENCODATION] += 17.0f / 4.0f;
249 }
250 else {
251 charCounts[EDIFACT_ENCODATION] += 13.0f / 4.0f;
252 }
253
254 // step Q
255 if (IsSpecialB256(c)) {
256 charCounts[BASE256_ENCODATION] += 4.0f;
257 }
258 else {
259 charCounts[BASE256_ENCODATION] += 1.0f;
260 }
261
262 //step R
263 if (charsProcessed >= 4) {
264 std::transform(charCounts.begin(), charCounts.end(), intCharCounts.begin(), [](float x) { return static_cast<int>(std::ceil(x)); });
265 FindMinimums(intCharCounts, std::numeric_limits<int>::max(), mins);
266 int minCount = std::accumulate(mins.begin(), mins.end(), 0);
267
268 if (intCharCounts[ASCII_ENCODATION] < intCharCounts[BASE256_ENCODATION]
269 && intCharCounts[ASCII_ENCODATION] < intCharCounts[C40_ENCODATION]
270 && intCharCounts[ASCII_ENCODATION] < intCharCounts[TEXT_ENCODATION]
271 && intCharCounts[ASCII_ENCODATION] < intCharCounts[X12_ENCODATION]
272 && intCharCounts[ASCII_ENCODATION] < intCharCounts[EDIFACT_ENCODATION]) {
273 return ASCII_ENCODATION;
274 }
275 if (intCharCounts[BASE256_ENCODATION] < intCharCounts[ASCII_ENCODATION]
276 || (mins[C40_ENCODATION] + mins[TEXT_ENCODATION] + mins[X12_ENCODATION] + mins[EDIFACT_ENCODATION]) == 0) {
277 return BASE256_ENCODATION;
278 }
279 if (minCount == 1 && mins[EDIFACT_ENCODATION] > 0) {
280 return EDIFACT_ENCODATION;
281 }
282 if (minCount == 1 && mins[TEXT_ENCODATION] > 0) {
283 return TEXT_ENCODATION;
284 }
285 if (minCount == 1 && mins[X12_ENCODATION] > 0) {
286 return X12_ENCODATION;
287 }
288 if (intCharCounts[C40_ENCODATION] + 1 < intCharCounts[ASCII_ENCODATION]
289 && intCharCounts[C40_ENCODATION] + 1 < intCharCounts[BASE256_ENCODATION]
290 && intCharCounts[C40_ENCODATION] + 1 < intCharCounts[EDIFACT_ENCODATION]
291 && intCharCounts[C40_ENCODATION] + 1 < intCharCounts[TEXT_ENCODATION]) {
292 if (intCharCounts[C40_ENCODATION] < intCharCounts[X12_ENCODATION]) {
293 return C40_ENCODATION;
294 }
295 if (intCharCounts[C40_ENCODATION] == intCharCounts[X12_ENCODATION]) {
296 size_t p = startpos + charsProcessed + 1;
297 while (p < msg.length()) {
298 int tc = msg.at(p);
299 if (IsX12TermSep(tc)) {
300 return X12_ENCODATION;
301 }
302 if (!IsNativeX12(tc)) {
303 break;
304 }
305 p++;
306 }
307 return C40_ENCODATION;
308 }
309 }
310 }
311 }
312}

314static std::string ToHexString(int c)
315{
316 const char* digits = "0123456789abcdef";
317 std::string val(4, '0');
318 val[1] = 'x';
319 val[2] = digits[(c >> 4) & 0xf];
320 val[3] = digits[c & 0xf];
321 return val;
322}

324namespace ASCIIEncoder {
325 /**
326 * Determines the number of consecutive characters that are encodable using numeric compaction.
327 *
328 * @param msg the message
329 * @param startpos the start position within the message
330 * @return the requested character count
331 */
332 static int DetermineConsecutiveDigitCount(const std::string& msg, int startpos)
333 {
334 auto begin = msg.begin() + startpos;
335 return static_cast<int>(std::find_if_not(begin, msg.end(), IsDigit) - begin);
336 }
337
338 static uint8_t EncodeASCIIDigits(int digit1, int digit2)
339 {
340 if (IsDigit(digit1) && IsDigit(digit2)) {
341 int num = (digit1 - '0') * 10 + (digit2 - '0');
342 return static_cast<uint8_t>(num + 130);
343 }
344 return '?';
345 }
346
347 static void EncodeASCII(EncoderContext& context)
348 {
349 //step B
350 int n = DetermineConsecutiveDigitCount(context.message(), context.currentPos());
351 if (n >= 2) {
352 context.addCodeword(EncodeASCIIDigits(context.currentChar(), context.nextChar()));
353 context.setCurrentPos(context.currentPos() + 2);
354 }
355 else {
356 int c = context.currentChar();
357 int newMode = LookAheadTest(context.message(), context.currentPos(), ASCII_ENCODATION);
358 if (newMode != ASCII_ENCODATION)
359 {
360 // the order here is the same as ENCODATION;
361 context.addCodeword(LATCHES[newMode]);
362 context.setNewEncoding(newMode);
363 }
364 else if (IsExtendedASCII(c)) {
365 context.addCodeword(UPPER_SHIFT);
366 context.addCodeword(static_cast<uint8_t>(c - 128 + 1));
367 context.setCurrentPos(context.currentPos() + 1);
368 }
369 else {
370 context.addCodeword(static_cast<uint8_t>(c + 1));
371 context.setCurrentPos(context.currentPos() + 1);
372 }
373 }
374 }
375
376} // ASCIIEncoder

378namespace C40Encoder {
379
380 static int EncodeChar(int c, std::string& sb)
381 {
382 if (c == ' ') {
383 sb.push_back('\3');
384 return 1;
385 }
386 if (c >= '0' && c <= '9') {
387 sb.push_back((char)(c - 48 + 4));
388 return 1;
389 }
390 if (c >= 'A' && c <= 'Z') {
391 sb.push_back((char)(c - 65 + 14));
392 return 1;
393 }
394 if (c >= '\0' && c <= '\x1f') {
395 sb.push_back('\0'); //Shift 1 Set
396 sb.push_back(c);
397 return 2;
398 }
399 if (c <= '/') {
400 sb.push_back('\1'); //Shift 2 Set
401 sb.push_back((char)(c - 33));
402 return 2;
403 }
404 if (c <= '@') {
405 sb.push_back('\1'); //Shift 2 Set
406 sb.push_back((char)(c - 58 + 15));
407 return 2;
408 }
409 if (c <= '_') {
410 sb.push_back('\1'); //Shift 2 Set
411 sb.push_back((char)(c - 91 + 22));
412 return 2;
413 }
414 if (c <= '\x7f') {
415 sb.push_back('\2'); //Shift 3 Set
416 sb.push_back((char)(c - 96));
417 return 2;
418 }
419 sb.append("\1\x1e"); //Shift 2, Upper Shift
420 int len = 2;
421 len += EncodeChar((char)(c - 0x80), sb);
422 return len;
423 }
424
425 static int BacktrackOneCharacter(EncoderContext& context, std::string& buffer, std::string& removed, int lastCharSize, std::function<int (int, std::string&)> encodeChar)
426 {
427 buffer.resize(buffer.size() - lastCharSize);
428 context.setCurrentPos(context.currentPos() - 1);
429 int c = context.currentChar();
430 lastCharSize = encodeChar(c, removed);
431 context.resetSymbolInfo(); //Deal with possible reduction in symbol size
432 return lastCharSize;
433 }
434
435 static void EncodeToCodewords(EncoderContext& context, const std::string& sb, int startPos) {
436 int c1 = sb.at(startPos);
437 int c2 = sb.at(startPos + 1);
438 int c3 = sb.at(startPos + 2);
439 int v = (1600 * c1) + (40 * c2) + c3 + 1;
440 context.addCodeword(static_cast<uint8_t>(v / 256));
441 context.addCodeword(static_cast<uint8_t>(v % 256));
442 }
443
444 static void WriteNextTriplet(EncoderContext& context, std::string& buffer)
445 {
446 EncodeToCodewords(context, buffer, 0);
447 buffer.erase(0, 3);
448 }
449
450 /**
451 * Handle "end of data" situations
452 *
453 * @param context the encoder context
454 * @param buffer the buffer with the remaining encoded characters
455 */
456 static void HandleEOD(EncoderContext& context, std::string& buffer)
457 {
458 int unwritten = (Size(buffer) / 3) * 2;
459 int rest = Size(buffer) % 3;
460
461 int curCodewordCount = context.codewordCount() + unwritten;
462 auto symbolInfo = context.updateSymbolInfo(curCodewordCount);
463 int available = symbolInfo->dataCapacity() - curCodewordCount;
464
465 if (rest == 2) {
466 buffer.push_back('\0'); //Shift 1
467 while (buffer.length() >= 3) {
468 WriteNextTriplet(context, buffer);
469 }
470 if (context.hasMoreCharacters()) {
471 context.addCodeword(C40_UNLATCH);
472 }
473 }
474 else if (available == 1 && rest == 1) {
475 while (buffer.length() >= 3) {
476 WriteNextTriplet(context, buffer);
477 }
478 if (context.hasMoreCharacters()) {
479 context.addCodeword(C40_UNLATCH);
480 }
481 // else no unlatch
482 context.setCurrentPos(context.currentPos() - 1);
483 }
484 else if (rest == 0) {
485 while (buffer.length() >= 3) {
486 WriteNextTriplet(context, buffer);
487 }
488 if (available > 0 || context.hasMoreCharacters()) {
489 context.addCodeword(C40_UNLATCH);
490 }
491 }
492 else {
493 throw std::logic_error("Unexpected case. Please report!");
494 }
495 context.setNewEncoding(ASCII_ENCODATION);
496 }
497
498 static void EncodeC40(EncoderContext& context, std::function<int (int, std::string&)> encodeChar, int encodingMode)
499 {
500 //step C
501 std::string buffer;
502 while (context.hasMoreCharacters()) {
503 int c = context.currentChar();
504 context.setCurrentPos(context.currentPos() + 1);
505 int lastCharSize = encodeChar(c, buffer);
506 int unwritten = static_cast<int>(buffer.length() / 3) * 2;
507 int curCodewordCount = context.codewordCount() + unwritten;
508 auto symbolInfo = context.updateSymbolInfo(curCodewordCount);
509 int available = symbolInfo->dataCapacity() - curCodewordCount;
510
511 if (!context.hasMoreCharacters()) {
512 //Avoid having a single C40 value in the last triplet
513 std::string removed;
514 if ((buffer.length() % 3) == 2 && available != 2) {
515 lastCharSize = BacktrackOneCharacter(context, buffer, removed, lastCharSize, encodeChar);
516 }
517 while ((buffer.length() % 3) == 1 && ((lastCharSize <= 3 && available != 1) || lastCharSize > 3)) {
518 lastCharSize = BacktrackOneCharacter(context, buffer, removed, lastCharSize, encodeChar);
519 }
520 break;
521 }
522
523 if ((buffer.length() % 3) == 0) {
524 int newMode = LookAheadTest(context.message(), context.currentPos(), encodingMode);
525 if (newMode != encodingMode) {
526 // Return to ASCII encodation, which will actually handle latch to new mode
527 context.setNewEncoding(ASCII_ENCODATION);
528 break;
529 }
530 }
531 }
532 return HandleEOD(context, buffer);
533 }
534
535 static void EncodeC40(EncoderContext& context)
536 {
537 EncodeC40(context, EncodeChar, C40_ENCODATION);
538 }
539
540} // C40Encoder

542namespace DMTextEncoder {
543
544 static int EncodeChar(int c, std::string& sb)
545 {
546 if (c == ' ') {
547 sb.push_back('\3');
548 return 1;
549 }
550 if (c >= '0' && c <= '9') {
551 sb.push_back((char)(c - 48 + 4));
552 return 1;
553 }
554 if (c >= 'a' && c <= 'z') {
555 sb.push_back((char)(c - 97 + 14));
556 return 1;
557 }
558 if (c >= '\0' && c <= '\x1f') {
559 sb.push_back('\0'); //Shift 1 Set
560 sb.push_back(c);
561 return 2;
562 }
563 if (c <= '/') {
564 sb.push_back('\1'); //Shift 2 Set
565 sb.push_back((char)(c - 33));
566 return 2;
567 }
568 if (c <= '@') {
569 sb.push_back('\1'); //Shift 2 Set
570 sb.push_back((char)(c - 58 + 15));
571 return 2;
572 }
573 if (c >= '[' && c <= '_') {
574 sb.push_back('\1'); //Shift 2 Set
575 sb.push_back((char)(c - 91 + 22));
576 return 2;
577 }
578 if (c == '\x60') {
579 sb.push_back('\2'); //Shift 3 Set
580 sb.push_back((char)(c - 96));
581 return 2;
582 }
583 if (c <= 'Z') {
584 sb.push_back('\2'); //Shift 3 Set
585 sb.push_back((char)(c - 65 + 1));
586 return 2;
587 }
588 if (c <= '\x7f') {
589 sb.push_back('\2'); //Shift 3 Set
590 sb.push_back((char)(c - 123 + 27));
591 return 2;
592 }
593 sb.append("\1\x1e"); //Shift 2, Upper Shift
594 int len = 2;
595 len += EncodeChar(c - 128, sb);
596 return len;
597 }

599 static void EncodeText(EncoderContext& context)
600 {
601 C40Encoder::EncodeC40(context, EncodeChar, TEXT_ENCODATION);
602 }

606namespace X12Encoder {
607
608 static int EncodeChar(int c, std::string& sb)
609 {
610 switch (c) {
611 case '\r':
612 sb.push_back('\0');
613 break;
614 case '*':
615 sb.push_back('\1');
616 break;
617 case '>':
618 sb.push_back('\2');
619 break;
620 case ' ':
621 sb.push_back('\3');
622 break;
623 default:
624 if (c >= '0' && c <= '9') {
625 sb.push_back((char)(c - 48 + 4));
626 }
627 else if (c >= 'A' && c <= 'Z') {
628 sb.push_back((char)(c - 65 + 14));
629 }
630 else {
631 throw std::invalid_argument("Illegal character: " + ToHexString(c));
632 }
633 break;
634 }
635 return 1;
636 }
637
638 static void HandleEOD(EncoderContext& context, std::string& buffer)
639 {
640 int codewordCount = context.codewordCount();
641 auto symbolInfo = context.updateSymbolInfo(codewordCount);
642 int available = symbolInfo->dataCapacity() - codewordCount;
643 context.setCurrentPos(context.currentPos() - Size(buffer));
644 if (context.remainingCharacters() > 1 || available > 1 || context.remainingCharacters() != available) {
645 context.addCodeword(X12_UNLATCH);
646 }
647 if (context.newEncoding() < 0) {
648 context.setNewEncoding(ASCII_ENCODATION);
649 }
650 }
651
652 static void EncodeX12(EncoderContext& context)
653 {
654 //step C
655 std::string buffer;
656 while (context.hasMoreCharacters()) {
657 int c = context.currentChar();
658 context.setCurrentPos(context.currentPos() + 1);
659 EncodeChar(c, buffer);
660 size_t count = buffer.length();
661 if ((count % 3) == 0) {
662 C40Encoder::WriteNextTriplet(context, buffer);
663
664 int newMode = LookAheadTest(context.message(), context.currentPos(), X12_ENCODATION);
665 if (newMode != X12_ENCODATION) {
666 // Return to ASCII encodation, which will actually handle latch to new mode
667 context.setNewEncoding(ASCII_ENCODATION);
668 break;
669 }
670 }
671 }
672 HandleEOD(context, buffer);
673 }
674
675} // X12Encoder

677namespace EdifactEncoder {
678
679 static void EncodeChar(int c, std::string& sb)
680 {
681 if (c >= ' ' && c <= '?') {
682 sb.push_back(c);
683 }
684 else if (c >= '@' && c <= '^') {
685 sb.push_back((char)(c - 64));
686 }
687 else {
688 throw std::invalid_argument("Illegal character: " + ToHexString(c));
689 }
690 }
691
692 static ByteArray EncodeToCodewords(const std::string& sb, int startPos)
693 {
694 int len = Size(sb) - startPos;
695 if (len == 0) {
696 throw std::invalid_argument("buffer must not be empty");
697 }
698 int c1 = sb.at(startPos);
699 int c2 = len >= 2 ? sb.at(startPos + 1) : 0;
700 int c3 = len >= 3 ? sb.at(startPos + 2) : 0;
701 int c4 = len >= 4 ? sb.at(startPos + 3) : 0;
702
703 int v = (c1 << 18) + (c2 << 12) + (c3 << 6) + c4;
704 int cw1 = (v >> 16) & 255;
705 int cw2 = (v >> 8) & 255;
706 int cw3 = v & 255;
707 ByteArray res;
708 res.reserve(3);
709 res.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(cw1));
710 if (len >= 2) {
711 res.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(cw2));
712 }
713 if (len >= 3) {
714 res.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(cw3));
715 }
716 return res;
717 }
718
719 /**
720 * Handle "end of data" situations
721 *
722 * @param context the encoder context
723 * @param buffer the buffer with the remaining encoded characters
724 */
725 static void HandleEOD(EncoderContext& context, std::string& buffer)
726 {
727 try {
728 size_t count = buffer.length();
729 if (count == 0) {
730 return; //Already finished
731 }
732 if (count == 1) {
733 //Only an unlatch at the end
734 int codewordCount = context.codewordCount();
735 auto symbolInfo = context.updateSymbolInfo(codewordCount);
736 int available = symbolInfo->dataCapacity() - codewordCount;
737 int remaining = context.remainingCharacters();
738 // The following two lines are a hack inspired by the 'fix' from https://sourceforge.net/p/barcode4j/svn/221/
739 if (remaining > available)
740 available = context.updateSymbolInfo(codewordCount+1)->dataCapacity() - codewordCount;
741 if (remaining <= available && available <= 2) {
742 return; //No unlatch
743 }
744 }
745
746 if (count > 4) {
747 throw std::invalid_argument("Count must not exceed 4");
748 }
749 int restChars = static_cast<int>(count - 1);
750 auto encoded = EncodeToCodewords(buffer, 0);
751 bool endOfSymbolReached = !context.hasMoreCharacters();
752 bool restInAscii = endOfSymbolReached && restChars <= 2;
753
754 if (restChars <= 2) {
755 int codewordCount = context.codewordCount();
756 auto symbolInfo = context.updateSymbolInfo(codewordCount + restChars);
757 int available = symbolInfo->dataCapacity() - codewordCount;
758 if (available >= 3) {
759 restInAscii = false;
760 context.updateSymbolInfo(codewordCount + Size(encoded));
761 //available = context.symbolInfo.dataCapacity - context.getCodewordCount();
762 }
763 }
764
765 if (restInAscii) {
766 context.resetSymbolInfo();
767 context.setCurrentPos(context.currentPos() - restChars);
768 }
769 else {
770 for (uint8_t cw : encoded) {
771 context.addCodeword(cw);
772 }
773 }
774 }
775 catch (...) {
776 context.setNewEncoding(ASCII_ENCODATION);
777 throw;
778 }
779 context.setNewEncoding(ASCII_ENCODATION);
780 }
781
782 static void EncodeEdifact(EncoderContext& context)
783 {
784 //step F
785 std::string buffer;
786 while (context.hasMoreCharacters()) {
787 int c = context.currentChar();
788 EncodeChar(c, buffer);
789 context.setCurrentPos(context.currentPos() + 1);
790
791 if (buffer.length() >= 4) {
792 auto codewords = EncodeToCodewords(buffer, 0);
793 for (uint8_t cw : codewords) {
794 context.addCodeword(cw);
795 }
796 buffer.erase(0, 4);
797
798 int newMode = LookAheadTest(context.message(), context.currentPos(), EDIFACT_ENCODATION);
799 if (newMode != EDIFACT_ENCODATION) {
800 // Return to ASCII encodation, which will actually handle latch to new mode
801 context.setNewEncoding(ASCII_ENCODATION);
802 break;
803 }
804 }
805 }
806 buffer.push_back(31); //Unlatch
807 HandleEOD(context, buffer);
808 }
809
810} // EdifactEncoder

812namespace Base256Encoder {
813
814 static int Randomize255State(int ch, int codewordPosition)
815 {
816 int pseudoRandom = ((149 * codewordPosition) % 255) + 1;
817 int tempVariable = ch + pseudoRandom;
818 if (tempVariable <= 255) {
819 return tempVariable;
820 }
821 else {
822 return tempVariable - 256;
823 }
824 }
825
826 static void EncodeBase256(EncoderContext& context)
827 {
828 std::string buffer;
829 buffer.push_back('\0'); //Initialize length field
830 while (context.hasMoreCharacters()) {
831 int c = context.currentChar();
832 buffer.push_back(c);
833
834 context.setCurrentPos(context.currentPos() + 1);
835
836 int newMode = LookAheadTest(context.message(), context.currentPos(), BASE256_ENCODATION);
837 if (newMode != BASE256_ENCODATION) {
838 // Return to ASCII encodation, which will actually handle latch to new mode
839 context.setNewEncoding(ASCII_ENCODATION);
840 break;
841 }
842 }
843 int dataCount = Size(buffer) - 1;
844 int lengthFieldSize = 1;
845 int currentSize = context.codewordCount() + dataCount + lengthFieldSize;
846 auto symbolInfo = context.updateSymbolInfo(currentSize);
847 bool mustPad = (symbolInfo->dataCapacity() - currentSize) > 0;
848 if (context.hasMoreCharacters() || mustPad) {
849 if (dataCount <= 249) {
850 buffer.at(0) = (char)dataCount;
851 }
852 else if (dataCount <= 1555) {
853 buffer.at(0) = (char)((dataCount / 250) + 249);
854 buffer.insert(1, 1, (char)(dataCount % 250));
855 }
856 else {
857 throw std::invalid_argument("Message length not in valid ranges: " + std::to_string(dataCount));
858 }
859 }
860 for (char c : buffer) {
861 context.addCodeword(Randomize255State(c, context.codewordCount() + 1));
862 }
863 }
864
865} // Base256Encoder

867static bool StartsWith(const std::wstring& s, const std::wstring& ss)
868{
869 return s.length() > ss.length() && s.compare(0, ss.length(), ss) == 0;
870}
871
872static bool EndsWith(const std::wstring& s, const std::wstring& ss)
873{
874 return s.length() > ss.length() && s.compare(s.length() - ss.length(), ss.length(), ss) == 0;
875}
876
877ByteArray
878HighLevelEncoder::Encode(const std::wstring& msg)
879{
880 return Encode(msg, SymbolShape::NONE, -1, -1, -1, -1);
881}

883/**
884* Performs message encoding of a DataMatrix message using the algorithm described in annex P
885* of ISO/IEC 16022:2000(E).
886*
887* @param msg the message
888* @param shape requested shape. May be {@code SymbolShapeHint.FORCE_NONE},
889* {@code SymbolShapeHint.FORCE_SQUARE} or {@code SymbolShapeHint.FORCE_RECTANGLE}.
890* @param minSize the minimum symbol size constraint or null for no constraint
891* @param maxSize the maximum symbol size constraint or null for no constraint
892* @return the encoded message (the char values range from 0 to 255)
893*/
894ByteArray
895HighLevelEncoder::Encode(const std::wstring& msg, SymbolShape shape, int minWdith, int minHeight, int maxWidth, int maxHeight)
896{
897 //the codewords 0..255 are encoded as Unicode characters
898 //Encoder[] encoders = {
899 // new ASCIIEncoder(), new C40Encoder(), new TextEncoder(),
900 // new X12Encoder(), new EdifactEncoder(), new Base256Encoder()
901 //};
902
903 EncoderContext context(TextEncoder::FromUnicode(msg, CharacterSet::ISO8859_1));
904 context.setSymbolShape(shape);
905 context.setSizeConstraints(minWdith, minHeight, maxWidth, maxHeight);
906
907 if (StartsWith(msg, MACRO_05_HEADER) && EndsWith(msg, MACRO_TRAILER)) {
908 context.addCodeword(MACRO_05);
909 context.setSkipAtEnd(2);
910 context.setCurrentPos(Size(MACRO_05_HEADER));
911 }
912 else if (StartsWith(msg, MACRO_06_HEADER) && EndsWith(msg, MACRO_TRAILER)) {
913 context.addCodeword(MACRO_06);
914 context.setSkipAtEnd(2);
915 context.setCurrentPos(Size(MACRO_06_HEADER));
916 }
917
918 int encodingMode = ASCII_ENCODATION; //Default mode
919 while (context.hasMoreCharacters()) {
920 switch (encodingMode) {
921 case ASCII_ENCODATION: ASCIIEncoder::EncodeASCII(context); break;
922 case C40_ENCODATION: C40Encoder::EncodeC40(context); break;
923 case TEXT_ENCODATION: DMTextEncoder::EncodeText(context); break;
924 case X12_ENCODATION: X12Encoder::EncodeX12(context); break;
925 case EDIFACT_ENCODATION: EdifactEncoder::EncodeEdifact(context); break;
926 case BASE256_ENCODATION: Base256Encoder::EncodeBase256(context); break;
927 }
928 if (context.newEncoding() >= 0) {
929 encodingMode = context.newEncoding();
930 context.clearNewEncoding();
931 }
932 }
933 int len = context.codewordCount();
934 auto symbolInfo = context.updateSymbolInfo(len);
935 int capacity = symbolInfo->dataCapacity();
936 if (len < capacity) {
937 if (encodingMode != ASCII_ENCODATION && encodingMode != BASE256_ENCODATION && encodingMode != EDIFACT_ENCODATION) {
938 context.addCodeword('\xfe'); //Unlatch (254)
939 }
940 }
941 //Padding
942 if (context.codewordCount() < capacity) {
943 context.addCodeword(PAD);
944 }
945 while (context.codewordCount() < capacity) {
946 context.addCodeword(Randomize253State(PAD, context.codewordCount() + 1));
947 }
948
949 return context.codewords();
950}
